# Backend: OpenSpec + Superpowers (per `CLAUDE.md`)

This rule applies when **any file under `backend/`** is in scope. Follow the project constitution in the repo root `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/CLAUDE.md`.

## OpenSpec (CLI + change folders)

- **Working directory**: run the `openspec` CLI from **`backend/`** (not repo root). Change folders live under **`backend/openspec/changes/<name>/`**.
- **Skill files** (read and follow before automating):  
  - `.claude/skills/openspec-propose/SKILL.md`  
  - `.claude/skills/openspec-apply-change/SKILL.md`  
  - `.claude/skills/openspec-archive-change/SKILL.md`  
  - `.claude/skills/openspec-explore/SKILL.md` (explore / unclear requirements)

### When to activate which step

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| **New backend feature**, new API behavior, schema/migration that changes contracts | **`/opsx:propose`** (or equivalent: `openspec new change …`, generate proposal/design/tasks per skill). **No implementation until the user approves** the proposal direction. |
| User approved / tasks exist and asks to **implement** | **`/opsx:apply`** — follow **openspec-apply-change**: `openspec status`, `openspec instructions apply`, work **`tasks.md`** in order with TDD. |
| Change is **fully implemented and merged** | **`/opsx:archive`** — follow **openspec-archive-change**. |
| Requirements fuzzy | **`/opsx:explore`** or **openspec-explore** skill before proposing. |

### Small / urgent fixes

Purely mechanical edits (comments, typo in string, formatting) may skip OpenSpec **propose**, but **any behavior or contract change** still warrants a change record when it is non-trivial; use judgment and prefer propose when unsure.

